"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140231","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-07-23","<p>£4.7 million of grant funding was announced on 12 June and made available through the Waste &amp; Resources Action Programme, to support new capital infrastructure projects that will help to recycle difficult plastic packaging and textile materials.</p><p> </p><p>The Government also incentivises business-led technology innovation through Innovate UK and its role to fund business-led innovation through the allocation of competitively awarded grants. This fund has previously supported chemicals recycling projects. Further details on Innovate UK are available at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/innovate-uk" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/innovate-uk</a>.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2019-07-23T15:51:05.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140231/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140231/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140231/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-07-18","Plastics: Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether he plans to increase support for catalytic chemical recycling and upcycling to realise the ambition of zero plastic waste.","false","Biography information for Paul Farrelly","Newcastle-under-Lyme","Paul Farrelly","278919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140232","Home Office","false","2019-07-22","<p>Information collected, collated and published in official statistics is kept under review, balancing user needs against burdens on suppliers, in accordance with the Code of Practice for Statistics, implementing the Statistics and Registration Act 2007 (copy available at <a href="https://www.statisticsauthority.gov.uk/code-of-practice/the-code/" target="_blank">https://www.statisticsauthority.gov.uk/code-of-practice/the-code/</a>).</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-07-22T16:15:21.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140232/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140232/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140232/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-07-18","Visas: Married People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 11 March 2019 to Question 229177 on visas: married people, if he will collate and publish figures for (a) the number of applications submitted under Appendix FM where the sponsor did not meet the financial requirement but argued that there were exceptional circumstances pertaining to their case and (b) the number of applications that were successful.","false","Biography information for Sir Henry Bellingham","North West Norfolk","Sir Henry Bellingham","278926"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140233","Home Office","false","2019-07-23","<p>There are currently 55 licences in extant to cultivate low THC cannabis (Industrial Hemp) in England, Wales and Scotland. <br>There are currently 2 licences in extant to cultivate low THC cannabis (Industrial Hemp) in Scotland.</p><p>The licences are generally issued for a validity period of three growing seasons and therefore will include licences issued in 2017, 2018 and 2019.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","279072","2019-07-23T15:01:58.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140233/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140233/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140233/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-07-18","Hemp: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many licences for the cultivation of industrial hemp are in effect in the UK.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","279071"
