"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140349","Department for Transport","false","2019-07-24","<p>TransPennine Express provides an hourly service between these cities which will soon be operated by brand new 125mph-capable intercity bi-mode trains.</p><p> </p><p>There is no requirement in the current Northern franchise agreement for Northern to run direct services from Liverpool to Newcastle.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2019-07-24T14:55:45.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140349/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140349/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140349/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-07-18","Northern","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, for what reasons there are no direct Northern rail services between Liverpool and Newcastle.","false","Biography information for Esther McVey","Tatton","Esther McVey","278985"
