"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140373","Home Office","false","2019-07-22","<p>The Tier 1 (General) route closed to Leave to Remain extension applications on 6 April 2015. Therefore, no Tier 1 General extension applications were received in the last twelve months.</p><p><br>The data regarding exceeding the eight-week service standards in current application routes can be found using the link <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-may-2019" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-may-2019 </a></p><p><br>The statistics specific to service standards can be found on tab InC_02.</p><p>Historical data regarding service standards can be found via the following link:<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data#previous-data-releases" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data#previous-data-releases</a></p><p>Complexity is identified on a case by case basis and will also vary depending on the application route. Therefore there is not an exhaustive list of the circumstances in which particular types of application might be deemed to be complex. Where an application is defined as non-straightforward, due to complexity, the customer will be written to within the normal processing time to explain why it will not be decided within the normal standard service, and to explain what will happen next.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","279031 ; 279032","2019-07-22T16:19:26.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140373/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140373/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140373/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-07-18","Visas: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate he has made of the number of applications received in each of the last twelve months for Leave to Remain extension application as a Tier 1 Highly Skilled general migrant; and how of those cases were concluded within eight weeks.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","279030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140374","Home Office","false","2019-07-22","<p>The Tier 1 (General) route closed to Leave to Remain extension applications on 6 April 2015. Therefore, no Tier 1 General extension applications were received in the last twelve months.</p><p><br>The data regarding exceeding the eight-week service standards in current application routes can be found using the link <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-may-2019" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-may-2019 </a></p><p><br>The statistics specific to service standards can be found on tab InC_02.</p><p>Historical data regarding service standards can be found via the following link:<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data#previous-data-releases" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data#previous-data-releases</a></p><p>Complexity is identified on a case by case basis and will also vary depending on the application route. Therefore there is not an exhaustive list of the circumstances in which particular types of application might be deemed to be complex. Where an application is defined as non-straightforward, due to complexity, the customer will be written to within the normal processing time to explain why it will not be decided within the normal standard service, and to explain what will happen next.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","279030 ; 279032","2019-07-22T16:19:26.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140374/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140374/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140374/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-07-18","Visas: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, for what reasons the processing of extension applications may exceed the eight-week agreed service standard; and with what frequency that standard has been exceeded in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","279031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140375","Home Office","false","2019-07-22","<p>The Tier 1 (General) route closed to Leave to Remain extension applications on 6 April 2015. Therefore, no Tier 1 General extension applications were received in the last twelve months.</p><p><br>The data regarding exceeding the eight-week service standards in current application routes can be found using the link <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-may-2019" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/in-country-migration-data-may-2019 </a></p><p><br>The statistics specific to service standards can be found on tab InC_02.</p><p>Historical data regarding service standards can be found via the following link:<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data#previous-data-releases" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data#previous-data-releases</a></p><p>Complexity is identified on a case by case basis and will also vary depending on the application route. Therefore there is not an exhaustive list of the circumstances in which particular types of application might be deemed to be complex. Where an application is defined as non-straightforward, due to complexity, the customer will be written to within the normal processing time to explain why it will not be decided within the normal standard service, and to explain what will happen next.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","279030 ; 279031","2019-07-22T16:19:26.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140375/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140375/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1140375/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-07-18","Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the reasons are that qualify an extension application as complex.","false","Biography 